<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> CNN Lands Mrs. Clinton Interview </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- CNN's Christiane Amanpour has won the first  
television interview with first lady Hillary Rodham Clinton in more 
than a year. 
</P>
<P>
	Amanpour was to speak to Mrs. Clinton today in Skopje,  
Macedonia, during her visit to refugee camps for people who have 
fled from Yugoslavia. CNN planned to show the interview at 10 p.m. 
EDT and again Saturday at 9:30 a.m. EDT, network spokeswoman 
Christa Robinson said. 
</P>
<P>
	Amanpour intends to focus her interview on Mrs. Clinton's role  
as an international envoy. Amanpour, who also works for CBS's ``60 
Minutes,'' is one of CNN's lead international reporters and has 
covered the Yugoslavian conflict since NATO bombing began. 
</P>
<P>
	The interview will also cover other topics, Ms. Robinson said.  
The first lady is considering a run for the U.S. Senate in New York 
next year. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Clinton's last one-on-one television interview was given to  
Matt Lauer of NBC's ``Today'' show on Jan. 27, 1998, after 
allegations of her husband's relationship with Monica Lewinsky 
first surfaced. 
</P>
</TEXT>
