<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Big Movers in the Stock Market  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks that moved substantially or traded  
heavily ...day on the New York Stock Exchange and Nasdaq Stock 
Market. 

</P>
<P>
                               *NYSE    	

</P>
<P>
 *AMR Corp., down 2 15/16 at 71 1/16    	
</P>
<P>
	The Justice Department Thursday sued American Airlines for  
allegedly trying to quash competition at its Dallas-Forth Worth 
hub. It's the first predatory pricing case since the government 
deregulated the industry in 1978. 

</P>
<P>
 *U S West Inc., up 2 1/4 at 62 1/4  
</P>
<P>
 *Global Crossing Ltd., down 5/8 at 59 3/8 in Nasdaq trading 
</P>
<P>
	Global Crossing, a provider of Internet and long-distance  
service, is in talks to buy U S West for as much as $35 billion in 
stock, CNBC reported. 

</P>
<P>
 *Caribiner International, down 1 11/16 at 5 15/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Caribiner, which provides business communications services and  
training programs, said it expects net income for the remainder of 
the fiscal year to be substantially below analysts' estimates. The 
company beat expectations for its second quarter, but said it 
expects only modest revenue growth for the rest of the year. 

</P>
<P>
 *Meadowcraft Inc., up 2 11/16 at 9 11/16    	
</P>
<P>
	An acquisition group led by Meadowcraft's chairman, Samuel R.  
Blount, will buy the stake it doesn't already own for $10 a share 
in cash, or about $53.2 million. Blount and his family now own 
about 73 percent of the company, which makes wrought-iron goods. 

</P>
<P>
                              *NASDAQ   	

</P>
<P>
 *3Com Corp., up 2 5/16 at 28 7/8    	
</P>
<P>
	Business Week magazine reported 3Com may be acquired, and cited  
rivals including Lucent Technologies as possible partners. The 
company, a maker of network equipment, has been a frequent target 
of speculation. 

</P>
<P>
 *Silknet Software.com, up 7 11/16 at 41 9/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Priceline.com Inc., an online seller of airline tickets and  
hotel reservations, adopted Silknet technology that allows 
electronic commerce companies to offer greater levels of customer 
self-service. 

</P>
<P>
 *Priceline.com Inc., up 11 5/16 at 132 13/16    	
</P>
<P>
	Priceline.com got a lift as Merrill Lynch increased its revenue  
estimates for the Web-based company. Merrill said it expects online 
ticket broker to have second-quarter revenues of $65 million, up 
from $60 million as originally forecast. For fiscal 1999, Merrill 
now expects revenues of $300 million, up from $265 million. 

</P>
<P>
 *Iridium World Communications, down 3 3/4 at 10 3/4    	
</P>
<P>
	The satellite phone company said it has hired an investment bank  
to help it review and restructure its debt. The Washington, 
D.C.-based company said it will not be able to meet key terms of 
its $800 million credit facility. 

</P>
<P>
 *Crescent Operating, up 2 1/4 at 6 1/8    	
</P>
<P>
	The diversified management company, with holdings in hotels,  
fitness centers and equipment leasing businesses, said Friday it 
earned 31 cents per share in its first quarter, reversing a loss of 
11 cents per share a year earlier. 

</P>
</TEXT>
