<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Formula One Changes Racing Calendar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	MONTE CARLO, Monaco (AP) -- Formula One racing is changing places  
in Britain and planning a return to France. 
</P>
<P>
	Bernie Ecclestone, the chief executive of Formula One, said  
Friday the British Grand Prix will move from Silverstone to Brands 
Hatch, England, in 2002. 
</P>
<P>
	He also he said his firm, Excelis, acquired the former home of  
the French Grand Prix, the Paul Ricard Circuit in southern France, 
and hopes to return Formula One racing there. 
</P>
<P>
	The announcements -- during an offday before qualifying for the  
Grand Prix of Monaco -- are the latest changes made by Formula One. 
</P>
<P>
	Last week, the date for the first U.S. Grand Prix at  
Indianapolis Motor Speedway was set for Sept. 24, 2000. The only 
Formula One race in North America now is the Canadian Grand Prix in 
Montreal in June. 
</P>
<P>
	For the British GP, Ecclestone said he was not able to reach an  
agreement with the owners of Silverstone, the British Racing 
Drivers Club, to hold the race beyond 2001, and made a six-year 
deal to bring the event back to Brands Hatch. 
</P>
<P>
	Brands Hatch Leisure Group, the owner of the racing circuit,  
about 30 miles from London, said they signed an exclusive contract 
with F1. 
</P>
<P>
	``I look forward to making this the biggest and most successful  
Grand Prix ever,'' said Nicola Foulston, the chief executive 
officer of BHL and daughter of the former owner of the track, John 
Foulston. Foulston was killed in a crash at Silverstone in 1987. 
</P>
<P>
	The owners of Brand Hatch said they are committed to more than  
$30 million to reconstruct the track and its facilities to bring it 
up to current Formula One standards. 
</P>
<P>
	Silverstone, about 60 miles from London, has held the British  
Grand Prix since 1987. Before that, the race alternated between 
Silverstone and Brands Hatch with five races at Aintree between 
1955 and 1962. 
</P>
<P>
	Britain staged the first event of the Formula One series in  
1950, and a British Grand Prix has been held every year since. 
</P>
<P>
	Also, Ecclestone's group announced the purchase of the Paul  
Ricard Circuit at Le Castellet near Toulon. 
</P>
<P>
	``We are going to make the circuit what it was, the best circuit  
in Europe,'' he said. 
</P>
<P>
	The French Grand Prix has been held in Magny Cours in central  
France since 1991, but has had contract difficulties over 
television rights and tobacco sponsorship. That made Formula One 
take the French GP off the calendar twice the past seven years 
before being reinstated. 
</P>
<P>
	Le Castellet opened in 1971, and hosted French Grand Prix 14  
times. It now is used for Formula One testing, and will hold the 
French Motorcycle Grand Prix next week. 
</P>
<P>
	``We are going to make a lot of repairs and a renovations so  
that it would be up to the standards and welcome the big races such 
as Formula One,'' Ecclestone said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
