<HEADLINE> Dow Falls 100 in Early Trading / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stock prices have opened lower. The Dow Jones  
Industrial Average is down 100 points in today's early going. 
Losers on the New York Stock Exchange hold a more than 4-1 lead 
over gainers. 
</P>
<P>
	The Nasdaq Composite Index is down 38 points and the S&AMP;P 500  
Index is down seven points. 
</P>
<P>
	The market's downward direction comes on the heels of an all-out  
plunge in the bond market. 
</P>
<P>
	The price on the benchmark 30-year bond is down nearly a point  
and three quarters, shooting the yield up to 5.88 percent. 
</P>
<P>
	That severe move is in reaction to this morning's  
higher-than-expected inflation numbers for April. 
</P>
<P>
	The government's consumer price index rose 0.7 percent last  
month. 
</P>
<P>
	And even though the markets are moving in fear of a rate hike  
from the Federal Reserve, economists believe that the Fed will most 
likely want to gather more information before making such a move. 
</P>
</TEXT>
