<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Mariners' Rodriguez Returns From DL </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SEATTLE (AP) -- Alex Rodriguez wasted little time getting back in  
the swing of things Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
	The Seattle Mariners shortstop, who missed 32 games with a torn  
medial meniscus in his left knee, homered in his first at-bat 
against Kansas City starter Jeff Suppan on a 2-0 pitch. 
</P>
<P>
	The three-time All-Star singled in his next at-bat in the third  
inning. He was later thrown out attempting to steal third. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodriguez was placed on the 15-day disabled list on April 19,  
retroactive to April 7. He originally suffered the injury March 30 
in Arizona. 
</P>
<P>
	Rodriguez left in the seventh inning of Seattle's second game of  
the season. He was 0-for-6 with a walk and one run entering 
Friday's game. The Mariners used seven shortstops in his absence. 
</P>
<P>
	The Mariners sent infielder Domingo Cedeno to Triple-A Tacoma to  
make room for Rodriguez. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
