<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Today In History  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Today is Saturday, May 15, the 135th day of 1999. There are 230  
days left in the year. 
</P>
<P>
	Today's Highlight in History:  
</P>
<P>
	On May 15, 1930, Ellen Church, the first airline stewardess,  
went on duty aboard a United Airlines flight between San Francisco 
and Cheyenne, Wyo. 
</P>
<P>
	On this date:  
</P>
<P>
	In 1602, Cape Cod was discovered by English navigator  
Bartholomew Gosnold. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1886, poet Emily Dickinson died in Amherst, Mass.  
</P>
<P>
	In 1911, the Supreme Court ordered the dissolution of Standard  
Oil Co., ruling it was in violation of the Sherman Antitrust Act. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1918, U.S. airmail began service between Washington,  
Philadelphia and New York. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1942, gasoline rationing went into effect in 17 states,  
limiting sales to three gallons a week for non-essential vehicles. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1948, hours after declaring its independence, the new state  
of Israel was attacked by Transjordan, Egypt, Syria, Iraq and 
Lebanon. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1963, U.S. astronaut L. Gordon Cooper blasted off aboard  
Faith Seven on the final mission of the Project Mercury space 
program. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1969, Supreme Court Justice Abe Fortas resigned amid a  
controversy over his past legal fees. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1972, George C. Wallace was shot by Arthur Bremer and left  
paralyzed while campaigning in Laurel, Md., for the Democratic 
presidential nomination. 
</P>
<P>
	In 1988, the Soviet Union began the process of withdrawing its  
troops from Afghanistan, more than eight years after Soviet forces 
had entered the country. 
</P>
<P>
	Ten years ago: Soviet President Mikhail S. Gorbachev arrived in  
Beijing for the first Sino-Soviet summit in 30 years, a visit 
overshadowed by pro-democracy demonstrations led by Chinese 
students. 
</P>
<P>
	Five years ago: Supreme Court nominee Stephen G. Breyer arrived  
in Washington to spend the night at the White House, while 
Republicans joined Democrats in predicting swift Senate 
confirmation. 
</P>
<P>
	One year ago: Trapped in blazing shopping malls, hundreds of  
looters burned to death in rioting that laid smoking waste to 
Indonesia's capital, Jakarta. 
</P>
<P>
	Today's Birthdays: Actress Constance Cummings is 89. Singer Eddy  
Arnold is 81. Actor Joseph Wiseman is 81. Playwright Anthony 
Shaffer (``Sleuth'') is 73. Playwright Peter Shaffer (``Amadeus'') 
is 73. Playwright Paul Zindel is 63. Actress-singer Anna Maria 
Alberghetti is 63. Counterculture icon Wavy Gravy is 63. Secretary 
of State Madeleine Albright is 62. Singer Trini Lopez is 62. Singer 
Lenny Welch is 61. Actress-singer Lainie Kazan is 59. 
Actor-director Paul Rudd is 59. Country singer K.T. Oslin is 57. 
Singer-songwriter Brian Eno is 51. Actor Chazz Palminteri is 48. 
Baseball player George Brett is 46. Actor Lee Horsley is 44. 
Singer-rapper Prince Be (PM Dawn) is 29. Actor David Charvet 
(``Melrose Place'') is 27. Rock musician Ahmet Zappa is 25. Olympic 
gold-medal gymnast Amy Chow is 21. 
</P>
<P>
	Thought for Today: ``Not to discover weakness is/The Artifice of  
strength...''-- Emily Dickinson, American poet (1830-1886). 

</P>
