<DOCNO> APW19990514.0054 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-05-14 16:08:57 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pippen Wants To Level Play  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- For Scottie Pippen, the Houston Rockets' playoff  
series with the Los Angeles Lakers has had more highs and lows than 
a roller coaster ride. 
</P>
<P>
	He came crashing down in the first two games, pointing fingers  
after the Game 1 loss and scoring just three points in Game 2 on 
0-of-7 shooting. 
</P>
<P>
	Pippen finally was back on top in Game 3 with a career-best 37  
points, helping the Rockets to a 102-88 victory Thursday night. 
</P>
<P>
	The question now is whether he can keep riding that high and  
help even the best-of-5 series at two games apiece, or is another 
fall on the horizon? Game 4 is Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't think I've ever lost my groove,'' Pippen said Friday  
after practice. ``I was just more aggressive last night, and I plan 
on being more aggressive throughout this series. 
</P>
<P>
	``Our manhood was on the line last night,'' he added. ``Letting  
this young team come out and really dominate us the first couple of 
games, we had to come out last night and prove that we're a team 
that deserves to be in the playoffs.'' 
</P>
<P>
	In the first two games, Pippen was 5-for-20 from the field,  
including 0-for-6 from 3-point range. In Game 3, he was 12-for-27 
from the field, including 3-for-5 on 3-pointers. 
</P>
<P>
	The Lakers' Kobe Bryant noticed a change.  
</P>
<P>
	``He came out more aggressive and did a better job of getting  
involved in their offense,'' Bryant said. ``He started going inside 
early and built up his confidence, and then he stepped back and 
started hitting the outside shots.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Bryant promised Pippen wouldn't get the same chance in Game 4.  
</P>
<P>
	``We've got to make our adjustments and counterattack on  
Saturday.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Shaquille O'Neal said Bryant would make things much tougher on  
Pippen next time. 
</P>
<P>
	``Kobe's coming back,'' he said. ``Scottie didn't have to play  
that much defense yesterday, but he's going to have to play defense 
tomorrow.'' 
</P>
<P>
	In Game 1, Bryant was guarding Pippen in the final seconds when  
Pippen lost his footing and control of the ball. The Lakers 
regained possession and went on to win 101-100. 
</P>
<P>
	After the game Pippen shifted the blame, questioning teammate  
Charles Barkley for fouling Shaquille O'Neal in the final minutes. 
Pippen then turned out a miserable Game 2 performance. 
</P>
<P>
	Barkley, shrugging off the earlier criticism, praised Pippen for  
turning things around in Game 3. 
</P>
<P>
	``I was very proud of my team,'' said Barkley, who had 30 points  
and 23 rebounds. ``Obviously, Scottie played great, and Brent Price 
and Sam Mack did, too.'' 
</P>
<P>
	In Game 3, O'Neal led the Lakers with 26 points and 10 rebounds,  
while Bryant and Glen Rice each had 13 points. At Friday's 
workouts, Rice complained that he should have gotten the ball more. 
</P>
<P>
	``The only thing I can do is try and go to the coach and ask him  
to run more plays for me,'' he said. ``I'm not going to go out 
there and break up a play to try and get Glen Rice involved. I just 
want it to happen in the flow of the offense.'' 
</P>
<P>
	O'Neal said the Lakers would simply have to get back to basics  
if they hope to lock up the series on Saturday. If the Rockets tie 
it, Game 5 would be Monday in Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
	``We've got to get back to what we were doing in Los Angeles,  
which is playing inside-outside and playing smart basketball,'' 
O'Neal said. ``If we play well, we should be OK.'' 
</P>
</TEXT>
