<HEADLINE> So. Ill. FB Player Killed in SUV </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	JACKSON, Miss. (AP) -- Southern Illinois wide receiver Charles  
Teague died Friday after the sport utility vehicle he was driving 
overturned several times on an interstate. 
</P>
<P>
	Teammate Brian Broussard, a defensive lineman who was with  
Teague, was treated at a hospital and released. 
</P>
<P>
	The two also had been teammates at St. Augustine High School in  
New Orleans. 
</P>
<P>
	Jackson police spokesman Robert Graham said the accident took  
place at 10:25 p.m. Thursday ``when for some undetermined reason 
the driver lost control of the vehicle, causing it to flip several 
times.'' 
</P>
<P>
	He said accident investigators were looking into the reasons for  
the fatal crash. 
</P>
<P>
	``An accident of this nature is devastating,'' said SIU head  
football coach Jan Quarless. ``We all -- coaches and players alike -- 
believe we are family which means we've lost a close member of our 
family. 
</P>
<P>
	``Charlie was a special person. He had never had many breaks in  
life, but had just recently been accepted into SIU's architectural 
technology school.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The 19-year-old Teague won a letter last season, had done well  
in spring drills and was expected to see a lot of action next 
season, according to Fred Huff, the sports information director at 
Southern Illinois. 
</P>
<P>
	Broussard was a defensive end last season but was being moved to  
an interior line position on defense. 
</P>
</TEXT>
