<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Quake Rocks Palm Springs Area </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PALM SPRINGS, Calif. (AP) -- A magnitude-5.0 earthquake shook the  
desert near Palm Springs early today. There were no immediate 
reports of damage or injuries from the aftershock to a deadly 1992 
temblor. 
</P>
<P>
	The earthquake happened at 12:54 a.m. and was centered 19 miles  
northeast of Palm Springs, said Joe Franck, a seismologist at the 
California Institute of Technology in Pasadena. 
</P>
<P>
	The initial quake was followed by a swarm of smaller tremors.  
Palm Springs is about 110 miles east of Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
	Gail Richardson, a clerk at the Joshua Tree sheriff's station,  
said deputies were fielding many calls from anxious residents but 
no one reported damage or injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	``It was felt throughout the entire basin, it was a pretty good  
one,'' Ms. Richardson said. 
</P>
<P>
	The magnitude-7.3 Landers earthquake struck June 28, 1992, and  
was followed a few hours later by a magnitude-6.5 quake hit in the 
San Bernardino Mountains. One person was killed. 
</P>
<P>
	There have been more than 70,000 aftershocks. This is the 24th  
aftershock with a magnitude of 5.0 or greater, Franck said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
