<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> TRW Adjusts Earnings To Show Loss </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CLEVELAND (AP) -- Automotive parts maker TRW Inc. revised its  
first-quarter earnings report to show a loss of $28.4 million 
instead of the profit of $58.6 million originally reported. 
</P>
<P>
	The adjustment disclosed Friday was related to an $85.3 million  
charge for acquiring British auto parts maker LucasVarity. TRW, 
which also makes defense equipment, bought LucasVarity for $7 
billion earlier this year. 
</P>
<P>
	TRW said its first-quarter earnings adjustment reflects a  
valuation of LucasVarity's research and development and a $1.7 
million increase in its income tax rate. 
</P>
<P>
	As a result, TRW's first-quarter earnings reported April 20 were  
reduced by $87 million for a net loss of $28.4 million, or 24 cents 
per share. That compares with net earnings of $129 million, or 
$1.03 per share, in the first quarter of 1998. 
</P>
<P>
	In afternoon trading on the New York Stock Exchange, TRW was off  
25 cents a share at $47.06 1/4. 

</P>
</TEXT>
