<HEADLINE> Mother, 3 Kids Found Dead in Tenn. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NASHVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- A woman who suffered hallucinations and  
thought everyone was out to get her killed her three children with 
a shotgun before taking her own life. 
</P>
<P>
	The bodies of the children, ages 4, 5 and 7, were found on a bed  
Thursday evening. Their mother, 28-year-old Tonya Avery, lay dead 
on the floor nearby. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Avery left a suicide note telling Danny Patterson, her  
boyfriend and father of the two girls, ``that she and the children 
loved him,'' police said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	The note gave no reason for the killings, but police said  
investigators were told Ms. Avery had ``exhibited recent signs of 
paranoia.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``She just started seeing and hearing things and everything, and  
thought that everybody was against her and thought that she was 
going to die,'' said Albert Davis, Ms. Avery's father. ``I just 
never thought it would come to this.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Police were called when a neighbor noticed that the home was  
unusually quiet and its front porch light had been on all day. 
</P>
