<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Sink; Dow Down 152.63 / Wall Street Report  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks plunged today after the government's  
report of a steep rise in consumer prices intensified worries about 
inflation and sent bond prices sharply lower. 
</P>
<P>
	At noon on Wall Street, the Dow Jones industrial average was  
down 152.63 at 10,954.56. Broader stock indicators were lower as 
well. 
</P>
<P>
	On Thursday, the Dow had climbed 106.82 to close at 11,107.19, a  
new record. 
</P>
<P>
	The selloff in stocks was sparked by the Labor Department's  
announcement that consumer prices rose 0.7 percent in April, the 
largest monthly gain in nearly nine years. The report was 
especially jarring following Thursday's producer-price report, 
which suggested inflation was subdued. 
</P>
<P>
	``The CPI is usually not out of line with that number,'' Barry  
Hyman, senior equity analyst at Ehrenkrantz King Nussbaum. ``This 
was a surprise.'' 
</P>
<P>
	The report led to a drop of more than two points in the price of  
the benchmark 30-year Treasury bond, pushing yields to 5.92 
percent, the highest level in nearly a year. 
</P>
<P>
	``The stock market is perfectly comfortable as long as bond  
yields are below 6 percent,'' said Hyman. ``But as the yield is 
nearing 6 percent, it won't be so comfortable.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Fears of inflation revived concerns that the Federal Reserve  
will at least consider an interest rate hike when its Open Market 
Committee meets next Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	The bond news pushed stocks of banking and financial companies  
lower. Chase Manhattan fell 4 to 80 on the New York Stock Exchange. 
Merrill Lynch fell 5 3/8 to 80 7/8. 
</P>
<P>
	IBM, which contributed to Thursday's new Dow record with a  
stunning 20-point gain, slipped 5 5/8 to 240 3/8, as investors locked in 
their gains. 
</P>
<P>
	The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 index was off 24.10 at 1,343.46, and  
the Nasdaq composite index was down 31.06 at 2,550.94. Nas 
</P>
<P>
	Declining issues outnumbered advancers by an 11-to-3 margin on  
the New York Stock Exchange, where volume came to 359 million 
shares, ahead of Thursday's pace. 
</P>
<P>
	The NYSE composite index was down 11.08 at 640.27, and the  
American Stock Exchange composite index was down 9.46 at 790.93. 




</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
