<HEADLINE> Woman Gets Prison for Death Plot </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PAPILLION, Neb. (AP) -- A woman was sentenced to three to 10  
years in prison Friday in the murder of her lover, who was stabbed 
to death for being too rough during group sex. 
</P>
<P>
	A pregnant Brandi Glynn, 20, had pleaded guilty to conspiracy to  
commit murder. 
</P>
<P>
	She is the first of six people to be sentenced in the killing of  
19-year-old Scott Catenacci. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Glynn sat in the victim's car Sept. 29 as he was stabbed  
more than 57 times at a park. 
</P>
<P>
	Catenacci was killed for roughing up an 18-year-old woman two  
weeks earlier during group sex that also involved Mrs. Glynn and a 
17-year-old man, prosecutors said. 
</P>
<P>
	Mrs. Glynn could have gotten 50 years in prison. Her lawyer  
refused to identify the father of her child. 
</P>
