<HEADLINE> Heat's Tim Hardaway Is Fined $5,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Miami's Tim Hardaway was fined $5,000 by the NBA  
today for failing to leave the court in a timely fashion and 
verbally abusing the officials following his ejection from Game 3 
of the Heat's playoff series against the New York Knicks. 
</P>
<P>
	Hardaway was automatically ejected after incurring two technical  
fouls during the Heat's 97-73 loss, which gave the Knicks a 2-1 
lead in the best-of-5 series. Game 4 is tonight at Madison Square 
Garden. 
</P>
<P>
	Hardaway, bothered by a sore right knee, has been disappointing  
in the series, shooting less than 19 percent from the field in the 
first three games and averaging only 7.3 points. He has made only 
one of 14 3-point field goals, and is averaging 4.0 turnovers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
