<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 2nd Dragging Death Trial Moved </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- The trial of the second defendant in the dragging  
death of a black man was ordered moved Friday from Jasper to the 
city of Bryan, 140 miles away. 
</P>
<P>
	The judge in the case previously decided to move the trial out  
of Jasper at the request both the defense and the prosecution. The 
defense argued that people in Jasper, where the crime took place, 
may be inclined to convict the defendant to salvage the town's 
image. 
</P>
<P>
	Jury selection will begin in early August for the trial of  
Lawrence Russell Brewer, with opening statements set for Aug. 30. 
Bryan is a city of 60,000 in Brazos County, about 80 miles 
northwest of Houston. 
</P>
<P>
	Brewer, 32, is one of three white men arrested in the June 7  
slaying of James Byrd Jr. The 49-year-old black man was chained to 
a pickup truck and dragged to pieces in a crime that shocked the 
nation. 
</P>
<P>
	The first man to be tried, 24-year-old John William King, was  
convicted and sentenced to death in Jasper earlier this year. 
</P>
<P>
	The third man, Shawn Allen Berry, will be tried later.  
</P>
</TEXT>
