<HEADLINE> Yugoslav Soccer Shifted to Greece </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NYON, Switzerland (AP) -- Yugoslavia will play next month's  
qualifying game for soccer's European Championships in Salonica, 
Greece, because of war in the Balkans. 
</P>
<P>
	The game against Malta will be June 8 or 9. European soccer's  
governing body said Friday that Malta and Yugoslavia agreed to the 
neutral site. 
</P>
<P>
	UEFA had said Yugoslavia remains eligible for Euro 2000 but  
cannot play at home. Yugoslavia resumes Group 8 qualifying play 
June 5 in Dublin against Ireland. 
</P>
<P>
	UEFA plans to review scheduling of Euro 2000 games involving  
Balkan countries when it meets May 25-26 in Barcelona, Spain. 
