<HEADLINE> Europe: Dollar, Gold Move Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LONDON (AP) -- The dollar fell against other major currencies in  
European trading today. Gold also was lower. 
</P>
<P>
	The euro was quoted at $1.0712, up from $1.0620 Thursday. The  
dollar was quoted at 122.04 Japanese yen, up from 121.42 yen. At 
midday in New York, the euro was quoted at $1.0654 and the dollar 
was quoted at 122.51 yen. 
</P>
<P>
	Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Thursday:  
1.4944 Swiss francs, down from 1.5022; 1.4590 Canadian dollars, 
down from 1.4614. The British pound was quoted at $1.6222, up from 
$1.6186. 
</P>
<P>
	Currencies of the 11 countries participating in the euro are no  
longer traded separately, though they remain in use. Based on euro 
rates, the dollar was worth: 1.8258 German marks, down from 1.8416; 
6.1236 French francs, down from 6.1766; 2.0572 Dutch guilders, down 
from 2.0751; 1,807.57 Italian lire, down from 1,823.23. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold closed in London at $275.90 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$277.30 on Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	In Zurich, where markets were closed Thursday, gold traded at  
$275.75 today. 
</P>
<P>
	Gold fell $1.50 in Hong Kong to $277.25.  
</P>
<P>
	Silver closed in London at $5.38 bid per troy ounce, down from  
$5.45. 
</P>
</TEXT>
