adjustment disclosed today was related to an $85.3 million charge 
for acquiring British auto parts maker LucasVarity. TRW, which also 
makes defense equipment, bought LucasVarity for $7 billion earlier 
this year. TRW said its first-quarter earnings adjustment reflects 
a valuation of LucasVarity's research and development and a $1.7 
million increase in its income tax rate. TRW shares were at 47 1/8, 
down 3/16. 

