<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	Rain showers and some thunderstorms were hovering over the Ohio  
Valley through lower Alabama and north Florida early today. 
</P>
<P>
	Elsewhere in the eastern United States, a low pressure area  
spinning near upper New England was bringing clouds to upper Maine. 
The remaining eastern third of the country was dry and partly 
cloudy this morning. 
</P>
<P>
	Most of the nation's central states were dry and clear to partly  
cloudy while mostly cloudy skies covered most of Montana, Wyoming, 
Idaho, Washington, Oregon, Utah, and Colorado. 
</P>
<P>
	Rain showers and thunderstorms were possible today in Virginia,  
east Georgia and Florida, with some areas of steady rain in the 
Carolinas. 
</P>
<P>
	A trough lingering through the Ohio Valley was expected to bring  
clouds and the chance for scattered showers in lower Ohio, lower 
Indiana, and east Kentucky and Tennessee. 
</P>
<P>
	In the West, there was a chance for scattered rain showers over  
Washington and Oregon, Idaho, Montana, Wyoming, Colorado, and Utah. 
</P>
<P>
	Some clouds were predicted for the northern parts of California  
and Nevada, with a slight chance for showers. The rest of the lower 
western states were likely to be dry and partly cloudy today. 
</P>
<P>
	The highest temperature reported in the continental United  
States on Thursday was 99 degrees at Luke, Ariz. The lowest was 21 
degrees at Saranac Lake, NY. 
</P>
<P>
	Highs today were expected to reach the 50s and 60s in the  
Northeast; 60s and 70s in the Plains states; and the 80s and 90s in 
parts of the West and Southwest. 
</P>
</TEXT>
