<HEADLINE> Garbo Ashes To Be Buried in Sweden </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) -- Greta Garbo's ashes will be buried in  
the city of her birth. 
</P>
<P>
	The reclusive film star died in New York City in 1990 at age 84.  
She was cremated and the ashes have been kept at a New York 
mortuary while her niece and sole heir, Gray Reisfield, decided 
what to do with them. 
</P>
<P>
	She has decided on Skogskyrkogaarden, the cemetery in Stockholm  
where Garbo's parents are buried, she said in a statement Friday. 
</P>
<P>
