<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Injury Forces Connors To Leave Match </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Jimmy Connors, just four points from victory  
against Jose-Luis Clerc, retired with a torn abdominal muscle 
Friday in the quarterfinals of the Sprint PCS Champions seniors 
tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	Connors was leading 6-3, 5-4 and would have been serving for the  
match when he requested trainer Bob Donatelli for the third time. 
Donatelli advised Connors to stop or face a six-month layoff if the 
injury got worse. 
</P>
<P>
	Afterward, Connors, lying on the training table with his right  
hand on his forehead and his left hand holding an ice pack on his 
ribs, said he first felt the injury while serving in the first set. 
In the second set, his serves were slow and short. 
</P>
<P>
	``After I played a couple of long points, I had problems taking  
deep breaths,'' Connors said. ``I was OK when I was down hitting my 
groundstrokes, but on my serve I wasn't getting any pace and it 
wasn't getting any better. If we just had a returning match out 
there, I'd have been OK.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Connors, who had won the tour's two previous tournaments and had  
a six-match winning streak, said he didn't try to finish the game 
to get the victory because he would have been forced to default in 
the next round. 
</P>
<P>
	``The people deserve some tennis on the weekend,'' Connors said.  
``If I'm not going out there 100 percent, it's not right for me to 
play. I'm not like that.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Clerc could only shrug his shoulders as he accepted the winner's  
applause leaving the court. 
</P>
<P>
	``I don't feel so happy because I beat Connors in this way,''  
Clerc said. ``I think it's really bad for the tournament because 
everybody wants to see Jimmy Connors. It's really difficult to play 
when you see somebody in pain.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Donatelli said Connors might be able to play in the tour's next  
event, June 8-13 in New York. 
</P>
<P>
	John McEnroe, the tournament's top seed, opens play Saturday  
against Mikael Pernfors, who beat Eddie Dibbs 6-4, 6-4. 
</P>
<P>
	Also Friday, Tim Wilkison defeated John Lloyd 6-0, 6-3 and Mats  
Wilander beat Mel Purcell 6-4, 7-6 (7-2). 
</P>
</TEXT>
