<HEADLINE> Burger King, Autogrill Team in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ROME (AP) -- Burger King Corp, a unit of Diageo PLC, and Italy's  
catering and restaurant group Autogrill SpA signed an agreement to 
jointly open 500 restaurants in Europe in the next 20 years, 
Autogrill said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	Autogrill, famous for cafes along Italian highways, manages 636  
restaurants and bars in nine European countries. 
</P>
<P>
	Burger King manages more than 10,000 restaurants around the  
world, including 885 in Europe, Autogrill said in a statement. 
</P>
<P>
	The accord also envisages Autogrill selling Burger King products  
in some of its outlets, the statement said. 

