<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> O'Donnell Making Tony Appearance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Rosie O'Donnell was too busy to host this year's  
Tony Awards. But a guest appearance? That she can manage. 
</P>
<P>
	The talk show host, who was the host for the ceremony the past  
two years, is scheduled to appear on the live June 6 broadcast 
along with Julie Andrews, Carol Burnett, Kevin Spacey, Jason 
Robards, Brian Dennehy, Scott Wolf and Stockard Channing. 
</P>
<P>
	``There will be several host-presenters, some of whom will be  
paired based on their theatrical ties, rather than a single star,'' 
Walter Miller, the show's executive producer, said Thursday. 
</P>
<P>
	The 53rd annual ceremony will be televised by CBS. O'Donnell was  
credited with improving the Tony show's ratings as host, but she 
declined to take the job for the third straight year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
