<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> 1 Dead in Mich. Truck Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DEARBORN, Mich. (AP) -- A 16-year-old who got his driver's  
license three days ago lost control and crashed a pickup truck 
packed with classmates, killing one and injuring 13, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	The driver and his passengers, ranging in age from 14 to 16,  
were freshman at Dearborn Edsel Ford High School in suburban 
Detroit, said police Chief Ronald Deziel. 
</P>
<P>
	The driver had halted at a stop sign Thursday, then rapidly  
accelerated before making a quick turn that caused the truck to 
turn on its side, Deziel said. 
</P>
<P>
	Some of the injured suffered broken bones, the chief said. All  
were released from a hospital by Thursday afternoon. 
</P>
<P>
	Justin Bailey, a 15-year-old rider in the truck's bed, landed in  
the street and was fatally run over by the vehicle, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	``We just tipped over and then everyone was flying everywhere,''  
said passenger Wesley Hartman. 
</P>
<P>
	The driver, who was not injured, was questioned by police and  
then released into the custody of his parents. It has not been 
determined what charges he will face, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	``At a minimum, he will be charged with reckless driving,''  
Deziel said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
